text.section:
When a carrier elects not to renew all individual health benefit plans in the State, the carrier:
shall give notice of its decision to the affected individuals at least 180 days before the effective date of nonrenewal;
at least 30 working days before that notice, shall give notice to the Commissioner;
if the carrier has an affiliate in the individual market, shall give notice to each affected individual at least 180 days before the effective date of nonrenewal of the individual's option to purchase all other individual health benefit plans currently offered by the affiliate of the carrier; and
may not write new business for individuals in the State for a 5-year period beginning on the date of notice to the Commissioner.
